description: When cubed gives number composed just of the digits 1, 2, 3, 4.
comments: No more terms through 10^13. [From _Jon E. Schoenfield_, Jul 03 2010]
mathematica: Do[ If[ Union[ Join[ {1, 2, 3, 4}, IntegerDigits[n^3] ]] == {1, 2, 3, 4}, Print[n]], {n, 0, 10^8} ]
author: _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jun 23 2001
